:["Tinned peaches and mangoes can be used in this recipe. They will not need to be steamed and can hold more liquid so you may need to cook the glaze a little longer (an extra <b>5 min\/100°C\/speed <b>) in step 3. Check the texture of your fruit; you may not need to blend it in step 4 if it's broken down quite a bit.","This chutney is lovely with chicken wings, lamb ribs and ham. You can also use it as a glaze when baking ham.","Store in sterilised jars to preserve it, or store in a sealable container in the refrigerator for up to 3 weeks."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","45m","1 total recipe"]}